    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-26T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-26T02:35:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90H/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-26T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 26, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 26—11:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. Referring to Department’s 157, December 13. The Afghan Government informs me
                    through its Ambassador Tehran that it agrees to the opening an AmLegation at
                    Kabul. It adds, however, that since diplomatic representatives accredited to
                    Afghanistan and those sent abroad by the Afghan Government have the rank of
                    Ambassador or Minister Plenipotentiary it is “preferable” that the American
                    Government designate a Minister Plenipotentiary to Afghanistan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
